# Notes App — Project Documentation

## Overview
Simple Laravel notes application with authentication. Technologies used:
- PHP (Laravel)
- JavaScript
- NPM / frontend assets
- Composer

## Quick requirements
- PHP 8+
- Composer
- Node.js & NPM
- MySQL / SQLite (configured in `.env`)

## Setup (fresh clone)
1. Copy environment:
   - `cp .env.example .env`
   - Configure DB and APP_URL in `.env`
2. Install PHP dependencies:
   - `composer install`
3. Install JS dependencies and build assets:
   - `npm install`
   - `npm run dev` (or `npm run build`)
4. Generate app key and migrate:
   - `php artisan key:generate`
   - `php artisan migrate`
5. Run the app:
   - `php artisan serve`

## Routes (summary)
Major routes are defined in `routes/web.php`:
- `GET /` — welcome page (public)
- `GET /dashboard` — dashboard (auth + verified)
- Notes (auth middleware):
  - `GET /notes` — list notes
  - `POST /notes` — create note
  - `GET /notes/{note}/edit` — edit form
  - `PUT /notes/{note}` — update
  - `DELETE /notes/{note}` — delete

Authentication routes are loaded from `routes/auth.php`.

## Change default post-login/registration redirect
If after login/registration users are redirected to `/dashboard` but you want `/`, change the `HOME` constant:
- File: `app/Providers/RouteServiceProvider.php`
- Change:
  - from: `const HOME = '/dashboard';`
  - to: `const HOME = '/';`

This updates `redirect()->intended(...)` targets used by auth controllers.

## Styling / dark theme issues
If the app uses a dark background and text is not visible on `/` (welcome page):
- Check `resources/views/welcome.blade.php` and other view files for text color classes or inline styles.
- Check your CSS (e.g. `resources/css/app.css` or Tailwind config) for body/background and text color.
- Common fixes:
  - Ensure text color contrasts the dark background (for example `color: #fff;` or Tailwind `text-white`).
  - If you changed a global CSS variable, verify it doesn't set `color: transparent` or same value as background.

Files to review/update:
- `resources/views/welcome.blade.php`
- Any layout or component views used by welcome/dashboard (for example `resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php`)
- `resources/css/app.css` or Tailwind config

## Troubleshooting checklist
- After changing `RouteServiceProvider::HOME`, clear caches:
  - `php artisan config:cache`
  - `php artisan route:cache`
  - `php artisan view:clear`
- If `/` renders but text is missing:
  - Inspect page HTML (browser DevTools) to confirm text exists in DOM.
  - If present but invisible, confirm CSS color/opacity and z-index.
  - If not present, confirm `welcome.blade.php` content and that the route returns the correct view.

